reviews.text:
Visited Hongkong 5 days, we came 3 days on a row, oops WEDNESDAY was closed , we knew this ahead but that morning my sister and I craving so much about the fish congee that we totally forgot about this !!!!!!
This place became the bucket list whenever we visit Hongkong from Canada since 2009, 2012, 2016, 2018 and 2019 . This is a must go place for breakfast in Cheung Chau . You will be addicted after you tried their fish congee, yau tiu( Chinese donut ) red bean cake , almond soya bean milk, etc . Price is reasonable and portion is bigger than average!!  WE WILL COME AGAIN!!

The two types of porridge we tried were fine in HK standard. The real star of the shop is the orange peel red bean pudding. It's unique, tastes good (if you like the Cantonese dehydrated orange peel) and with the right texture and consistency. If I go Cheung Chau again, I'll head straight there for this divine dessert.  Mind you it's an acquired taste!
Decent food and inexpensive.   Will visit again.
Good place for a nice traditional Breakfast by the bay...

A very good place for tasting a Hong Kong style Breakfast. Fair price with large portion translates into good value. As shown in my photo is youTiao, which means oil stick in Cantonese. We will eat this with congee of your own choice, maybe also with soy milk. Although it os becoming less common due to lack of profit(both food are low in margin), it is undeniably a part if our local culture, try it if you like experiencing local culture.

reviews.text: 還不錯吃，跟台灣的有一點不同，有淡淡的米味，清清淡淡微甜這樣，比較重口味些的就加白胡椒粉，會更鮮甜，價錢也不貴，HK$24是粥的平均價，我吃皮蛋瘦肉粥，點餐請講仔細哦，還有一個是皮蛋塩肉粥，然後魚片粥要小心魚片都是有些小刺的，但我看店家是直接去對面的市場帶回魚片XD我想新鮮是可以想見的。老闆人很好還問我們好不好吃，結完帳還送我們吃一個紅豆做的甜點，台灣沒見過的，愛吃紅豆的人應該會愛，口感蠻札實，也不會過甜，感謝老闆的收買XD位置在一出港口後往右走，再往海邊走就能見到lo，會先經過張記魚蛋麵

以香港物價水準而言，物美價廉！
跟多數當地攤販一樣沒有冷氣，吃粥會覺得熱。
假期🎏完結,一早已經食完B&B 早餐,美食邊有人話夠,行一個圈,見到這間出名舊式🍚粥店,當然要食一碗,係長洲當然叫一碗長洲🛶艇仔粥,一個咸煎餅,兒時味道,一碟炒🍜米粉,粥好棉,完全冇味精,調味當然係自己放塩同胡椒粉,咸煎餅有南乳味道,外面少見,外面連鎖店完全不同.😋
